title: It looks like some old fashioned kind of comic or comedy tittle
author: endlose

comments.content: It appears to be [Fontdinerdotcom Jazz Dark](http://web.archive.org/web/20140826014135/http:/old.myfonts.com/fonts/fontdiner/fontdinerdotcom-jazz-dark/)- filled in.
A bit boder but looks like [Loungy](http://web.archive.org/web/20140826014135/http:/www.dafont.com/fontdinerdotcom-lou.font) by Fontdiner.
I definitely disagree on this one, Ryuk. Jazz Dark filled in matches perfectly. Loungy will not match no matter what is done with it (just look at the L alone).
You're definitely right, Mike. Already got the point ;D
Not trying to be competitive, Ryuk. I'm happy to see a perfect match no matter who makes it (and _often_ impressed by your wide scope of expertise).

No worries, Mike. Tried to make a bit of humor ;)  
But I really enjoy everything here and I like the competition, not against all other identifiers and type experts but against my self ignorance. Frustration is key to me, I want to know them all!
